						<div class="postbody">I have decided to use a pointer to the ROM to make my emulator faster. I have everything setup, apart from the value of the PC itself.
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">*CPU.PC = 0x69 // ADC Immediate<br />&amp;CPU.PC = Address</div>
<br />
<br />How do I calculate the value of the PC ($0000-FFFF)? I need it for pushing and popping the PC for JSR/RTS and for the function that handles memory mapping. I have managed to do some kind of 'Current Address - Start Address' kind of thing but have only come up with 0x2C, which seems odd.</div>

